Golden parity fixtures for the pre-tool-use hook: ONE fixture set verified by
BOTH implementations in pre-commit/CI.

- Go: internal/hooks/pretooluse_test.go (TestPreToolUse_ParityFixtures) — byte-for-byte.
- JS: scripts/hooks/parity-contract.test.js — spawns the real hook process; byte-for-byte,
  except the fail-open parse-error fixture where the reason is prefix-matched
  ("The safety hook could not inspect this tool call:") because JSON parser error
  suffixes are implementation-specific.

Adding a fixture here extends the contract for both runtimes at once. Never fix a
parity mismatch by editing only the fixture: decide the canonical behavior first,
change the lagging implementation, then (only if the contract itself changed) the fixture.
